&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Point Wild helps customers monitor, manage, and protect against the risks associated with their identities and personal information in a digital world. Backed by WndrCo, Warburg Pincus and General Catalyst, Point Wild is dedicated to creating the world’s most comprehensive portfolio of industry-leading cybersecurity solutions. Our vision is to become THE go-to resource for every cyber protection need individuals may face - today and in the future.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Join us for the ride!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking a fully remote accounting and reporting manager to oversee the company’s complex accounting function and operations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll be accountable for ensuring accurate financial reporting for a global company by focusing on accounting for both operational and complex transactions. You will lead the preparation of the financial statements, while assisting with global audits, and assist with enhancing internal controls to ensure accuracy of the company’s reported financial results.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Controller, you will work cross functionally with other departments across the organization, and will be instrumental in managing the company through a period of transition and transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day to day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly, quarterly and annual consolidated financial statements for the global consolidated group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the financial statement audit providing technical accounting memos and calculations for complex transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with building out internal controls and accounting processes in a global company to support audit requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review journal entries and account reconciliations against supporting documentation to ensure accounting accuracy within the financial statements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist FP&amp;amp;A with forecasting process and recognition of revenue and expenses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support day to day accounting operations by reviewing journal entries and providing management and support to staff as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage third party valuation experts on ASC 805 valuations for acquisitions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;M&amp;amp;A accounting including net working capital, purchase accounting for asset and stock purchases&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Equity accounting including stock based compensation, preferred equity, and warrants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the table:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in accounting or finance and CPA required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6-8 years of accounting and/or finance experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3-4 years of “Big 4” public accounting experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of accounting experience in an enterprise SaaS organization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;M&amp;amp;A (buy side and sell side) and Technical Accounting experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Workday ERP&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Point Wild is committed to offering a generous package to support our employees in all aspects of their life in and out of work. Our packages offer competitive pay, generous health and wellness benefits, retirement savings plans, parental leave and much more! Pay range for this position is $135,000 - $150,000 but may vary depending on job-related knowledge, skills, experience and location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-Remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Point Wild helps customers monitor, manage, and protect against the risks associated with their identities and personal information in a digital world. Backed by WndrCo, Warburg Pincus and General Catalyst, Point Wild is dedicated to creating the world’s most comprehensive portfolio of industry-leading cybersecurity solutions. Our vision is to become THE go-to resource for every cyber protection need individuals may face - today and in the future.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Join us for the ride!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking a hands-on VPN &lt;strong&gt;Backend Architect (Golang)&lt;/strong&gt; to lead our backend team while spending 70% of your time writing Golang code. You&#39;ll set technical direction for our backend platform serving millions of users, guide an engineering team, and own architecture decisions for distributed services that must be fast, reliable, and secure at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role suits someone who wants to design secure, scalable systems and write the code that runs them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve the architecture of our backend platform serving connections from millions of users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build highly available distributed services in Golang while setting technical direction on scalability, reliability, and performance targets&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead code reviews and champion testing discipline, clean architecture, and engineering best practices across the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the SDK team to integrate client features cleanly into backend systems and deliver end-to-end functionality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor engineers and grow the technical depth of the team while collaborating with security, infrastructure, and product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the team to meet performance targets and ship reliable products that protect users at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of backend engineering &amp;amp; architecture experience with 5+ years in Golang&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record designing and operating distributed systems at scale with &lt;strong&gt;deep understanding of networking protocols&lt;/strong&gt; (IP, TCP, UDP, HTTP/HTTPS, DNS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with &lt;strong&gt;VPN protocols&lt;/strong&gt; (WireGuard, OpenVPN, IPsec), tunneling, NAT traversal, and low-latency networking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Production experience on &lt;strong&gt;AWS&lt;/strong&gt; (EC2, EKS, S3, Aurora/RDS) with &lt;strong&gt;container technologies&lt;/strong&gt; (Docker, Kubernetes) and &lt;strong&gt;strong Linux &lt;/strong&gt;development background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of cryptography fundamentals, threat modeling methodologies, secure coding practices, and strong API design skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master&#39;s degree in Computer Science or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network performance tuning and optimization experience with knowledge of &lt;strong&gt;Python and Java&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with NoSQL databases and familiarity with observability tools &lt;strong&gt;(Prometheus, Grafana, OpenTelemetry)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-REMOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As part of Point Wild, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solv

